keywords = {ontological models, knowledge graphs, relationship extraction, heterogenous data integration},
abstract = {Large enterprises usually operate with numerous autonomous data sources, each utilizing diverse storage schemes and underlying technological infrastructures. This can lead to the inability of data analysis at a high level and a violation of the integrity and reliability of data within the organization, hindering the adoption of high-quality decisions and further development of the company. To address this issue, we propose a methodology that represents heterogeneous organization data in a high-level space by combining them into single ontology represented by knowledge graph. The graph is constructed autonomously using semi-structured data from various sources. Our method identifies links between sources based on several similar metric between keys sets of each collection. Then document collections are combined into merged entities if collections’ key sets are similar. The experiments demonstrate the applicability of the developed approach for constructing a knowledge graph based on partially structured data from various sources, performing with high F1 measure (0.8 on average) when compared to the expert markup.}
}

